=== 自主及道德問題 ===
{{Main|機械倫理學}}

隨著機器人越來越複雜，專家及學者開始關注機器人的行為需符合哪一種[[倫理學|倫理學]]<ref name="AAAI ethics">[http://www.aaai.org/AITopics/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/AITopics/Ethics AAAI webpage of materials on robot ethics] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110805002115/http://www.aaai.org/AITopics/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/AITopics/Ethics |date=2011-08-05 }}.</ref>，以及哪一種機器人有資格擁有社會、文化、道德或是法律上的權利<ref>[http://www.aaai.org/AITopics/newstopics/ethics5.html AAAI compilation of articles on robot rights] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406094358/http://www.aaai.org/AITopics/newstopics/ethics5.html |date=2012-04-06 }}, Sources compiled up to 2006.</ref>。有一些科學組織宣稱在2019年可能就會有機器人的大腦<ref>[http://www.familyhealthguide.co.uk/scientists-predict-artificial-brain-in-10-years.html Scientists Predict Artificial Brain in 10 Years] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091129103022/http://www.familyhealthguide.co.uk/scientists-predict-artificial-brain-in-10-years.html |date=2009-11-29 }}, by Kristie McNealy M.D. July 29, 2009.</ref>。其他人預測機器人的智能在2050會有突破性的進展<ref name="Moravec2000">{{cite book|author=Hans Moravec|title=Robot Mere Machine to Transcendent Mind|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fduW6KHhWtQC|year=2000|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-513630-2|access-date=2014-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120621005702/http://books.google.com/books?id=fduW6KHhWtQC|archive-date=2012-06-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。最近的進展已經讓機器人的行為變得更加複雜<ref>[http://www.koreaittimes.com/story/4668/robots-almost-conquering-walking-reading-dancing Robots Almost Conquering Walking, Reading, Dancing] {{Wayback|url=http://www.koreaittimes.com/story/4668/robots-almost-conquering-walking-reading-dancing |date=20110721092117 }}, by Matthew Weigand, Korea Itimes, Monday, August 17, 2009.</ref>。2010年有一部名為《{{link-en|插头与祷告|Plug & Pray}}》的[[紀錄片|紀錄片]]，其中一個主題就是智能機器人對社會的衝擊<ref>[http://www.plugandpray-film.de/en/content.html ''Plug & Pray] {{Wayback|url=http://www.plugandpray-film.de/en/content.html |date=20160212040134 }}, documentary film by Jens Schanze about the possibilities of AI and robotics.</ref>。

[[弗諾·文奇|弗諾·文奇]]認為有一天電腦和機器人會比人更聰明，他稱之為「[[技術奇異點|奇異點]]」<ref name="nytimes july09">[http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/26/science/26robot.html?_r=1&ref=todayspaper Scientists Worry Machines May Outsmart Man] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/26/science/26robot.html?_r=1&ref=todayspaper |date=20150415135235 }} By John Markoff, ''The New York Times'', July 26, 2009.</ref>。他認為那時對人類會有某種程度的危險，也可能相當危險<ref>[http://www-rohan.sdsu.edu/faculty/vinge/misc/singularity.html The Coming Technological Singularity: How to Survive in the Post-Human Era] {{Wayback|url=http://www-rohan.sdsu.edu/faculty/vinge/misc/singularity.html |date=20070101133646 }}, by Vernor Vinge, Department of Mathematical Sciences, San Diego State University, (c) 1993 by Vernor Vinge.</ref>，在一種稱為{{link-en|奇点主义|Singularitarianism}}的哲學中會探討這個議題。

===戰爭機器人===
有些專家及學者質疑在戰爭中是否可以使用機器人，特別是有自主功能的機器人<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/8182003.stm Call for debate on killer robots] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/8182003.stm |date=20090807005005 }}, Jason Palmer. BBC News, August 3, 2009.</ref>。也有一些關注是有關可以讓軍事機器人受另一個機器人控制的技術<ref>[http://www.wired.com/dangerroom/2009/08/robot-three-way-portends-autonomous-future/ Robot three-way portends autonomous future] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/dangerroom/2009/08/robot-three-way-portends-autonomous-future/ |date=20121107102140 }}, By David Axe  wired.com, August 13, 2009.</ref>。美國海軍資助的一個計劃提出，隨著[[軍事機器人|軍事機器人]]越來越複雜，應該更重視其能力對作出自主決定的影響<ref>[http://www.dailytech.com/New%20Navyfunded%20Report%20Warns%20of%20War%20Robots%20Going%20Terminator/article14298.htm New Navy-funded Report Warns of War Robots Going "Terminator"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailytech.com/New%20Navyfunded%20Report%20Warns%20of%20War%20Robots%20Going%20Terminator/article14298.htm |date=20090728101106 }}, by Jason Mick (Blog), dailytech.com, February 17, 2009.</ref><ref>[http://www.engadget.com/2009/02/18/navy-report-warns-of-robot-uprising-suggests-a-strong-moral-com/ Navy report warns of robot uprising, suggests a strong moral compass] {{Wayback|url=http://www.engadget.com/2009/02/18/navy-report-warns-of-robot-uprising-suggests-a-strong-moral-com/ |date=20141006072301 }}, by Joseph L. Flatley  engadget.com, February 18, 2009.</ref>。有一個研究者認為自主機器人會更加有人性，因此可以更有效的作決定，但也有研究者質疑上述的想法<ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/layout/set/print/content/view/print/279448 New role for robot warriors;]{{dead link|date=December 2013}} Drones are just part of a bid to automate combat. Can virtual ethics make machines decisionmakers?, by Gregory M. Lamb, ''The Christian Science Monitor'', February 17, 2010.</ref>。

